Fred Itua, Abuja The National Assembly Service Commission (NASC), has instructed bureaucrats in the Service who have attained 35 years of service or 60 years of age, to proceed on a compulsory retirement. In a letter addressed to the affected staff, including the Clerk to the National Assembly, Mohammed Sani-Omolori, chairman of NASC, Ahmed Kadi Amshi, said the decision is in line with the 2014 amended Act of the Service. Beside Sani-Omolori, about 150 other staff are expected to exit the Service Iâ€™m line with the Act establishing NASC. 